    "body": "So I believe what happened is an edge case, as far as I understood from the info:\r\n- user A has `device A`  and have bought  `device B`\r\n- user C created group chat and send invite link to user A\r\n- user A has requested access via group chat invite link\r\n- user A was offline on `device B` for a while (probably more > 24h). During this time he was added as an admin of group chat \r\n- user A tried to access group chat via link on `Device B` - `Request pending` is shown\r\n- group chat has never appeared on `Device B` or on `Device A`\r\n\r\nSo User C has no option to remove user from group chat (he was added as admin), User A has no option to access group, as accessing via link shows `Request pending`\r\n\r\n**Suggested solution:**\r\nIf user was already added to group chat and access it via group link, show Group chat itself instead `Request pending`.\r\nWhat do you think @cammellos is it possible? \r\n",
